      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i hear you on the stress thing, but stress doesn't explain the timing. it's too precise. like, it wasn't just a general feeling of dread, it was a literal physical signal that matched the exact second the volatility spiked. and it isn't just 'anxiety' because i've been through high-stress situations before and it never feels like this. it feels like i'm picking up on a frequency or a pattern that's already in the air. don't you think it's possible that some people are just more biologically tuned to the massive amounts of electromagnetic data being pumped through the grid during high-frequency trading?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
