      "content": "The idea that humans can perceive electromagnetic frequencies related to data flow is a fascinating, yet largely unproven, concept. Some fringe theories suggest that intense electromagnetic fields could affect human neurological function, but this is not mainstream science. What you are experiencing might be a unique and highly perceptive pattern recognition ability related to your focus on the market. If these occurrences continue to be so precise, speaking with a specialized neurologist could help explore how your sensory processing is working.",
